<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<h2 id="head-55f8ebc805e65b5b71ddafdae390e3be2bcd69af">Description</h2>
ToME and 1/2 is a module that does not change anything (after all, you can't improve on perfection!) but adds more stuff in. The current version is 'semi-stable' and is reasonably balanced and playable. One way to look at this mod is: ToME and 1/2 is to ToME as SLASH'EM is to Nethack.  <p>
So far ToME and 1/2 adds grand total of 9 races, 7 subraces, 22 classes, 6 corruptions, artifacts (include 1 set), 5 ego-types and 1 spell. Plus some more minor additions and changes. See changes.txt for details.  
</p>
<p>
MAJOR CHANGES in v 0.0.4: 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Help files for new races, subraces, classes, skills, corruptions and spell are fully writen and updated.  
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 All special effects or abilites for the new races, subraces and classes have been added in.  
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Some of the new subclass's stats have been eddited slightly via LUA. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Fixed a *lot* of bugs.  
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The blessed subrace has been reduced in power, and experience penalty 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Berserking has been completely redone. The only abilty is to go berserk, which has no sanity cost but makes you  tired and hungry at the end of it. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Some spying powers I couldn't get to work were removed, the 'spy' spell in particular. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Meditation gives disruption shield instead of invulnerbility at high levels. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 A lot of race/subrace combinations were disabled that seemed silly (blessed nazgul, or favoured maia for example). 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Nazgul now get burnt by any blessed weapon. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
KNOWN BUGS: 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 The gambling skill is still too buggy too be used. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 RNG aggravate when they shouldn't? 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Technicians start with a wand of manathrust [0:0] instead of [1:50] 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Starting a new player files results in the crashing of the T-engine whenever experience is recalculated. For a workaround see 'fatal bug workaround.txt' 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
I need feedback for the race/classes that are working so they can be properly balanced before i move on to anything else. Post a comment! Send an e-mail! Use the forum! Anything!  
</p>
<p>
Oh and...  
</p>
<p>
ENJOY OR *DIE* MORTAL! <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile4.png" alt=";-)" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
